  <title translate="true">Picture Property</title>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">Picture Property</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Specifies an image to be displayed on the control.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Inline heading"><text styleclass="Inline heading" translate="true">Syntax</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Code Example"><text styleclass="Code Example" translate="true">Object.Picture = cFileName</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Inline heading"><text styleclass="Inline heading" translate="true">Parameters</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Parameter"><text styleclass="Parameter" translate="true">cFileName</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Explanation"><text styleclass="Explanation" translate="true">Specifies the name of the image file. The file must be in one of the formats supported by the .NET framework control. </text></para>
    <para styleclass="Inline heading"><text styleclass="Inline heading" translate="true">Compatibility</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">If the image file can neither be located inside the EXE nor as an external file, Guineu does not show anything at all. This is different from </text><var styleclass="Normal">&lt;%VFP%&gt;</var><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> where a non-existing image is shown as a crossed out rectangle.</text></para>
  </body>
